		<td class="contentheading" width="100%">
					Public Voting			</td>
	
	
		<td align="right" width="100%" class="buttonheading">
	<a href="/index.php?view=article&amp;id=9:public-voting&amp;tmpl=component&amp;print=1&amp;layout=default&amp;page=" title="Print" onclick="window.open(this.href,'win2','status=no,toolbar=no,scrollbars=yes,titlebar=no,menubar=no,resizable=yes,width=640,height=480,directories=no,location=no'); return false;" rel="nofollow"><img src="/images/M_images/printButton.png" alt="Print"  /></a>	</td>
	
		<td align="right" width="100%" class="buttonheading">
	<a href="/index.php/component/mailto/?tmpl=component&amp;link=aHR0cDovL3d3dy5ldXJvcGVhbi1nYW1lcy1hd2FyZC5jb20vaW5kZXgucGhwL2NvbXBvbmVudC9jb250ZW50L2FydGljbGUvOS1wdWJsaWMtdm90aW5n" title="E-mail" onclick="window.open(this.href,'win2','width=400,height=350,menubar=yes,resizable=yes'); return false;"><img src="/images/M_images/emailButton.png" alt="E-mail"  /></a>	</td>
		</tr>
</table>
<table class="contentpaneopen">




<tr>
<td valign="top" colspan="2">
<p>The European Games Award made an European-wide public voting possible for the first time. More than 12,000 Users registered at the EGA website and not only voted for the best action, sports, adventure game etc., they also also took part in the EGA-lottery. The first prize <strong>was an PS3, exclusively branded in the European Games Award Design</strong>.</p></td>
</tr>



</table>
<span class="article_separator">&nbsp;</span>

<table class="contentpaneopen">
<tr>
		<td class="contentheading" width="100%">
					Gamesload European Newcomer Award			</td>
	
	
		<td align="right" width="100%" class="buttonheading">
	<a href="/index.php?view=article&amp;id=4:gamesload-european-newcomer-award&amp;tmpl=component&amp;print=1&amp;layout=default&amp;page=" title="Print" onclick="window.open(this.href,'win2','status=no,toolbar=no,scrollbars=yes,titlebar=no,menubar=no,resizable=yes,width=640,height=480,directories=no,location=no'); return false;" rel="nofollow"><img src="/images/M_images/printButton.png" alt="Print"  /></a>	</td>
	
		<td align="right" width="100%" class="buttonheading">
	<a href="/index.php/component/mailto/?tmpl=component&amp;link=aHR0cDovL3d3dy5ldXJvcGVhbi1nYW1lcy1hd2FyZC5jb20vaW5kZXgucGhwL2NvbXBvbmVudC9jb250ZW50L2FydGljbGUvNC1nYW1lc2xvYWQtZXVyb3BlYW4tbmV3Y29tZXItYXdhcmQ%3D" title="E-mail" onclick="window.open(this.href,'win2','width=400,height=350,menubar=yes,resizable=yes'); return false;"><img src="/images/M_images/emailButton.png" alt="E-mail"  /></a>	</td>
		</tr>
</table>
<table class="contentpaneopen">




<tr>
<td valign="top" colspan="2">
<p>With the Gamesload European Newcomer Award your team has the chance to win 2.500 € as prize money as well as a European-wide distribution deal with Gamesload if you achieve the first place.<br />Here are the guidelines for a successful submission to the award:</p>
<p> </p>
<ul>
<li>Your game has been developed by university students, was a student’s project or was created and developed by a team of independent developers.</li>
<li>Your team members are older than 16 years and have not yet worked in a professional game developer studio or as freelancer in the games industry.</li>
<li>Your project is not a commissioned work for a professional developer and has not yet been released in any distributional channels.</li>
<li>Your project is not encumbered with third persons’ rights, you own all rights to your project.</li>
<li>Your project must at least exist in a playable version (beta version, prototype) as a whole or in parts (levels), which gives an idea of the game’s concept. You may also include trailers, videos or screenshots to complete the game’s impression</li>
<li>The entry deadline for a successful submission is July 26th 2010.</li>
<li>Awardees can be students, young professional developers, branch newcomers, natural persons or legal entities, it they are authorized to accept the award for its proper use.<br /></li>
<li>We reserve the right to cancel your submission to the award without further explanation even if all guidelines have been kept.<br /></li>
<li>Your project must have been developed for the PC.</li>
</ul>
<p><br />If you want to submit a game or have any questions concerning the <strong>Gamesload European Newcomer Award</strong> you can contact us via email to 
